# IRQ N has been injected into the guest N times via the IOAPIC
# info irq prints per-IRQ delivery counters for the interrupt controllers that QEMU/KVM emulates.
(qemu) info irq
info irq
IRQ statistics for kvm-ioapic:
 0: 153
 1: 11
 4: 21689
 8: 1
11: 27162
12: 125
14: 9130
15: 2386
IRQ statistics for kvm-i8259:
 0: 153
 1: 11
 4: 21689
 8: 1
11: 27162
12: 125
14: 9130
15: 2386





# NOTE:
Why you see both kvm-ioapic and kvm-i8259
Because x86 supports two interrupt routing models:
Legacy PIC (8259)
      |
      +--> cascaded to
            |
            v
        IOAPIC

Early boot
    Linux starts in PIC mode
    IRQs go via 8259
Later
    Linux switches to IOAPIC
    IRQs go via IOAPIC redirection table
    QEMU keeps both counters so you can see:
    Legacy compatibility behavior
    Modern interrupt routing

Same IRQ numbers appear because they represent the same logical lines, just through different controllers.
